-- Argentina Doesn’t Plan Multiple Exchange Rates, Fernandez Says
-- B y   E l i a n a   R a s z e w s k i
-- 2012-05-16T11:33:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/argentina-doesn-t-plan-multiple-exchange-rates-fernandez-says.html
Argentina has no plans to introduce
multiple exchange rates, President  Cristina Fernandez de
Kirchner  said, commenting on a report in newspaper El Cronista
yesterday.  “Can people really believe this?” Fernandez said last
night in a speech in  Buenos Aires , according to the  presidential
website . “It is this president who make decisions and she is
totally responsible and predictable.”  Yesterday, newspaper El Cronista reported that deputy
Economy Minister Axel Kicillof is studying a plan to apply three
different exchange rates to be used by importers, exporters and
by the financial system and tourism.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eliana Raszewski in Buenos Aires at 
 eraszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
